task.summary: weka experimentation branch - currently looks like will be too slow

- more successful fpgrowth can create predictions. Probably going to leave incomplete as association rules can only be printed, and interfacing with java and storing java object training data is messy enough without adding text parsing

- prediction using MLPClassifier implemented - accuracy is not great - test data is very skewed towards requesting course 2 - students request courses they have already taken - students don't often request courses along their degree path - more tuning needs to be done
fixed jinja error for nonexistent variable in assign-instructors
- only top k suggestions given, where k is the number of instructors that can be assigned - suggestions based on expected number/fraction of all requests for each course
- assign instructors bug fix for sql statement crash

- navigation bar now allows you to return to simulation flow on pages not part of simulation flow (academic record, success management) - Logo placeholder in navbar takes you back to navigation flow - fix incorrect pages saved as part of navigation flow
- refactored so user's current progress/page saved explicitly per page rather than in a separate function (prevents weird errors with triggers on script/image loads)
- order by clause removed from success-management
- fix for postgresql differences + more success-management cleanup
